{"parentUuid":null,"isSidechain":true,"promptId":"8a0970a7-992a-482d-b1fb-9fa84d4f1b3d","agentId":"a13995f3207b5009a","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"Cleanup finder, angles: EFFICIENCY + ALTITUDE (combined). Repo: c:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test. Scope = full uncommitted change-set vs HEAD (metric-quotas feature). EFFICIENCY: wasted work on the hot POST /v1/events path (redundant queries per request — e.g. is the quota lock+read executed even for tenants with no quota row every request, and could a cheaper existence probe come first? repeated I/O, blocking work at startup, sequential independent awaits), plus test-suite waste (per-test containers where session-scope would do). Note: strict-enforcement two-statement lock-then-read is load-bearing and human-approved — do not propose merging it; measured cost is ~3ms. ALTITUDE: fixes implemented as special cases where the mechanism should generalize — e.g. quota enforcement wired inline in events_service vs a middleware/dependency layer, app_code as a bolt-on attr vs a typed error hierarchy, the worker-parity guard as a bespoke test vs harness-level config, scope gating as an inline check in the quotas route vs a reusable require_scope dependency (events.py may grow scopes later). failure_scenario = concrete cost (per-request latency, maintenance).\nReturn up to 6 candidates: file, line, summary, cost. If none, say none."},"uuid":"0ab333dd-6898-4dc5-8ebe-762231d4fa85","timestamp":"2026-07-09T03:58:42.027Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"c:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
